---
import { evidenceStats } from '../data/research';
import Cite from './Cite.astro';
---

<section id="proof">
  <h2 class="section-title">✅ PROOF IT ACTUALLY WORKS ✅</h2>
  <p class="center comic">
    Not a testimonial. Not a guru. A preregistered randomized controlled trial.
  </p>

  {
    evidenceStats.map((s) => (
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat__value">{s.value}</span>
        <span class="stat__label">
          {s.label}
          <Cite source={s.source} />
        </span>
      </div>
    ))
  }

  <div class="inset">
    <p style="margin:0 0 6px">
      In the 2025 <b>PNAS Nexus</b> study, researchers had 467 people block
      mobile internet on their phones for two weeks — turning a smartphone into a
      de facto dumb phone. The reduction in depressive symptoms was
      <b>larger than what's typically seen with antidepressants</b>, and on par
      with a course of CBT.<Cite source="pnasNexus" />
    </p>
    <p style="margin:0" class="small muted">
      You don't have to go that far to benefit — but it's a striking demo of how
      much of the weight our phones quietly carry.
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr class="rainbow-hr" />
</section>
